    • Method Detail

      • createConsumer

        <K,V> PartitionConsumer<K,V> createConsumer(java.util.Properties properties,
                                            java.lang.Object keyDeserializer,
                                            java.lang.Object valueDeserializer)
        Creates consumer with key/value-decoder/deserializer instances passed. Discouraged in favor of createConsumer(Properties) which doesn't require to create deserializer instances.
        Type Parameters:
        K - - key class
        V - - value class
        Parameters:
        properties - - consumer properties, see ConsumerConfig for the details. For Kafka 08 only listed properties are supported, for greater versions all consumer properties.
        keyDeserializer - - implementation-specific decoder/deserializer for the key
        valueDeserializer - - implementation-specific decoder/deserializer for the key
        Returns:
        configured partition consumer

      • createConsumer

        Type Parameters:
        K - - key class
        V - - value class
        Parameters:
        properties - - consumer properties, see ConsumerConfig for the details
        Returns:
        configured partition consumer with dynamically created and configured key/value deserializers
